timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com
timelineItems.text: Still plenty of time for #NERevs to climb back. That said, they can't waste whatever chances come their way, esp. in the heat.

timelineItems.name: Julian Cardillo
timelineItems.text: #NERevs need a little bit of a spark here. Not much organized attack thus far. #DALvNE

timelineItems.desc: The New England Revolution go deep in the heart of Texas to face FC Dallas.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: FC Dallas vs. New England Revolution | July 4, 2015

timelineItems.name: Kyle McCarthy
timelineItems.text: In Frisco tonight. July 4 has not treated Revs well traditionally. New England sure could use result, though. #DALvNE

timelineItems.name: Julian Cardillo
timelineItems.text: Two positions that need depth asap: right back and center back. #DALvNE

timelineItems.desc: The New England Revolution go deep in the heart of Texas to face FC Dallas.

timelineItems.desc: Mauro Diaz scores a goal and two assists in victory against New England
timelineItems.title: MAURO DIAZ SHOW: Argentine star scores one and sets up another two

timelineItems.name: Julian Cardillo
timelineItems.text: Poorly executed play, but Caldwell really gaining confidence to go forward in shoot this season. #DALvNE

timelineItems.name: Ed Porter
timelineItems.text: #DALvNE I don't think Woodbury is as good as everyone says. He's already made some costly errors in this game.

timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com

timelineItems.name: Julian Cardillo
timelineItems.text: Much better in second half thus far for #NERevs...feel like an equalizer is on the cards #DALvNE

timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com
timelineItems.text: First five minutes of the second half #NERevs had 78.6% possession to just 21.4% for #FCDallas. Whatever Heaps said at HT working so far.

timelineItems.name: JT Chang
timelineItems.text: Difference between Rowe and Fagundez? Rowe makes that late run at the far post that Caldwell was looking for #NERevs
